  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/7608756/" class="title-link">道德的形而上学是可能的。</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-7608756"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/50896903/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img1.doubanio.com/icon/u50896903-8.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/50896903/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">Maël</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2015-09-26"
      class="main-meta">2015-09-26 18:58:40</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_7608756_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  重新反思Adam和Eva的故事。宗教语境下，身份标识的预置，开启了人类道德救赎的大门。疯子Nietzsche大胆定义人类“自戕”的历史，声嘶力竭痛斥基督教虚伪的奴隶道德，妄图基于超人哲学的浪漫想象，重新发明人之为人的全部含义。情绪化的呐喊固然振奋人心，但理性沉思的苦闷终究...

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">1有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_7608756_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_7608756_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
